arStrings.szText: Follow the Burned Knight candidate as he completes his pilgrimage.

A young man named Chairul wants to become a Burned Knight. He believes they will accept him if he proves himself worthy and wants me to act as a witness to his deeds. If I play along, I may be able to talk him out of this foolishness.
Bring Chairul to the first task

A young man named Chairul wants to become a Burned Knight. He believes they will accept him if he proves himself worthy and wants me to act as a witness to his deeds. If I play along, I may be able to talk him out of this foolishness.
Bring Chairul to the second task

A young man named Chairul wants to become a Burned Knight. He believes they will accept him if he proves himself worthy and wants me to act as a witness to his deeds. If I play along, I may be able to talk him out of this foolishness.
Bring Chairul to the final task

There were more Hollows in the cave than Chairul expected, and I stepped in to help when he panicked. Despondent, he has decided he's not worthy of joining the Burned Knights. While I failed to convince him of their evil, at least he will be safe. I should check in with him again at Kurast Docks.
Return to Chairul at the Docks
Chairul went with some Burned Knights to their camp. I should find him before something happens.
Search for Chairul at the Burned Knight camp
